.TH SIMPLE SHELL "09-01-2025" "1.0" "simple shell man page"

.SH NAME
simple shell - create a UNIX command interpreter.

.SH SYNOPSIS
simple shell
followed by a command

.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is a custom command-line interpreter that provides n user interface for UNIX-like operating systems, which executes commands from the standard input.

.SH EXAMPLES
./hsh
[command] [argument(s)]

$ ls -a

.SH ARGUMENTS
simple_shell
command arguments will be typed after the main command followed by a space and a '$' symbol.

.SH RETURN VALUE
On success the shell returns the result of the command typed into it. If there is an error it will return an error message or will exit itself.

.SH BUGS
In case of bugs, please report them to the authors of this project.

.SH AUTHORS
Brenda Pollagba, Gabriel Cohen
